**Read this whole file before doing anything else.**

## The project

`aa` is a Go CLI for managing Fly.io compute. Primary command is `aa docker up <path>` — build a Dockerfile and land in a shell on Fly in one command. Plus lifecycle commands (`aa machine spawn/ls/stop/rm/attach`, `aa docker image build/push/ls/rm`, `aa config`).

**Hard constraints (all architecture decisions assume these):**
- Go stdlib only. No third-party runtime or test deps. Enforced.
- Solo dev, LLM-authored. Philosophy: `v1/docs/PHILOSOPHY.md` — axes Clarity > Evolvability > Observability > Low-ceremony > Safety-at-boundary.
- Tool shells out to `flyctl` (SSH attach) and `docker` (image build). Both in preflight.

